title: For Sale:  Springfield WW2 (receiver) M1 Garand
postcontent:
(springfield as in the military arsenal, not the corporate brand/importer that has made some pretty crappy M1 Garands in recent years with cast receivers) 

I have a CMP Field Grade (although this could very well be a service grade in terms of quality and wear/tear) Springfield Receiver (ww2 manufactured 1943) M1 Garand with a WW2 trigger guard. Stock is a P proofed military replacement stock and the barrel is a replacement Springfield 1953. (I have a sneaking suspicion this rifle was manufactured during WW2 and might have been in Korea, only to be re-arsenaled once it got home in the early 50s) Shoots well, I have not shot at paper, but out to 150 yards I have been hitting pop cans and such with the iron sights.

Muzzle reading of 3 and Throat of 4 from the CMP. I have since measured it and gotten 2 and a little bit more than 3. CMP measures rather liberal. Military specs for a service rifle are less than 10/10.

title: For Sale:  Pre-ban Sites Spectre HC 9mm Pistol w/Pelican 1450, 1/30rnd, 2/50rnd + sling
postcontent:
Sites Spectre Falcon/HC pistol chambered in 9mm, manufactured in Italy and imported in 1991. The Spectre HC was banned in 1994 after only a few thousand were imported, making it difficult to find and hard to put a price on. I can assure you that you will not find another Spectre for sale anywhere in the region - you won't even find anything on Armslist besides one magazine for the .40cal variant.

The Spectre HC is a civilian model of the Spectre M4, a full auto SMG utilized by Police and Military forces in Italy. The Spectre is a standard blowback firearm operating from a closed bolt; however it has some unusual features. The barrel shroud completely hides the barrel. The bolt is designed to pump air through the barrel shroud to provide additional cooling. The Spectre is hammer-fired and the trigger group is double action with a decocker. This allows the shooter to safely carry a round in the chamber and fire immediately as the double action trigger eliminates the need for cocking prior to shooting. A manual safety is provided. Weighs 6lbs unloaded, and measures about 14 inches in length. In other words a compact, high capacity SHTF firearm. Barrel is about 5 inches, effective range is 150m or about 500 feet.

- This sale will include -
$1200 - Spectre HC in 9mm, with one 30rnd mag, two 50rnd mags, a Pelican 1450 case, a speed loader, and a single point bungee sling. The 50rnd clips will come in their original boxes, and I can also provide the original box for the Spectre. I will also include approximately 50 loose hollow point rounds.
